lobbying_activities:
[{'general_issue_code': 'TAX', 'general_issue_code_display': 'Taxation/Internal Revenue Code', 'description': 'Support of expanding the Coverdell Education Savings Account to include homeschool expenses, and also to expand 529 Plans to include k-12 homeschool expenses. Support of expanding the Child Tax Credit. Support of H.R. 2624, the Military Child Educational Freedom Act, introduced by Congressman Joe Wilson, which will expand Coverdell Education Savings Accounts for military families who homeschool their children.

Support of H.R.1, the Tax Cuts and Jobs Act, due to its doubling of the Child Tax Credit. HSLDA strongly supported the Ted Cruz Amendment which would have expanded 529 plans to homeschool expenses.

Meetings with Congressional staff, White House staff, staff to the Vice President, and Department of Education staff to oppose language such as in H.R. 610 which would give federal vouchers to homeschoolers. HSLDA opposes this because it could lead to future regulations on homeschoolers.', 'foreign_entity_issues': '', 'lobbyists': [{'lobbyist': {'id': 45127, 'prefix': 'mr', 'prefix_display': 'MR.', 'first_name': 'WILLIAM', 'nickname': None, 'middle_name': 'ANTHONY', 'last_name': 'ESTRADA', 'suffix': None, 'suffix_display': None}, 'covered_position': None, 'new': False}], 'government_entities': [{'id': 32, 'name': 'Education, Dept of'}, {'id': 11, 'name': 'Executive Office of the President (EOP)'}, {'id': 2, 'name': 'HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES'}, {'id': 13, 'name': 'Office of the Vice President of the United States'}, {'id': 1, 'name': 'SENATE'}, {'id': 39, 'name': 'State, Dept of (DOS)'}, {'id': 220, 'name': 'U.S. Commission on International Religious Freedom'}, {'id': 12, 'name': 'White House Office'}]}, {'general_issue_code': 'FAM', 'general_issue_code_display': 'Family issues/Abortion/Adoption', 'description': 'Meeting with Members of Congress and their staff about the Parental Rights Amendment to the US Constitution, which would enshrine parental rights as a fundamental right into the text of the US Constitution. 

Meetings with Members of Congress and their staff in support of the Parental Rights Amendment, which is S.J.Res. 48 in the Senate and H.J. Res. 121 in the House. Seeking cosponsors of the the Parental Rights Amendment.

Urging staff for the President and Vice President to withdraw the United States as a signatory from the UN Disabilities Treaty and the UN Convention on the Rights of the Child, as both of these treaties threaten US sovereignty and parental rights.

Meetings with Members of Congress and their staff about the need to amend CAPTA (the Child Abuse Prevention and Treatment Act) and ASFA (the Adoption and Safe Families Act) to better protect family integrity and Constitutional rights of innocent families.', 'foreign_entity_issues': '', 'lobbyists': [{'lobbyist': {'id': 45127, 'prefix': 'mr', 'prefix_display': 'MR.', 'first_name': 'WILLIAM', 'nickname': None, 'middle_name': 'ANTHONY', 'last_name': 'ESTRADA', 'suffix': None, 'suffix_display': None}, 'covered_position': None, 'new': False}], 'government_entities': [{'id': 32, 'name': 'Education, Dept of'}, {'id': 11, 'name': 'Executive Office of the President (EOP)'}, {'id': 2, 'name': 'HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES'}, {'id': 13, 'name': 'Office of the Vice President of the United States'}, {'id': 1, 'name': 'SENATE'}, {'id': 39, 'name': 'State, Dept of (DOS)'}, {'id': 220, 'name': 'U.S. Commission on International Religious Freedom'}, {'id': 12, 'name': 'White House Office'}]}, {'general_issue_code': 'IMM', 'general_issue_code_display': 'Immigration', 'description': "Alerting Members of Congress and their staff and the Executive Branch about the threat to homeschool freedom internationally.

Meetings with USCIRF on this issue.

Urging the US to grant asylum to persecuted homeschoolers in Cuba, or to put sanctions on Cuba, for that nation's persecution of homeschooling. Support of H.R. 391 which includes HSLDA's language to grant up to 500 individuals per year asylum in the United States, if they are facing persecution overseas because of their decision to homeschool, or be homeschooled.
